-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/koks-group-arranges-530-million-in-loans-from-russia-s-sberbank.html
OAO Koks, a Russian pig-iron and
coal producer, arranged to borrow $530 million from state-run
OAO Sberbank, regulatory filings show.  The bank will provide $400 million over seven years and
$130 million over five years to Koks unit Tulachermet in central
 Russia , according to the filings. Other Koks units will provide
repayment guarantees, according to the documents, dated
yesterday.  Koks scrapped a planned London share sale in February and
sold $350 million of dollar bonds in June to help cut debt and
fund expansion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
